| {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background:#C0EFBA\" align=\"left\" | {{sortname|Karl|Thieme|nolink=1}}+\n| [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] || <span style=\"display:none\">14-H</span>''[[Hauptmann]]''<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || Commander of the I./Panzergrenadier-Regiment 110<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p421\"/><ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || {{dts|format=dmy|1943|October|30}}<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || Awarded 627th Oak Leaves 23&nbsp;October&nbsp;1944<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/><br>{{fontcolor||#ffdead;|(156th) Swords 9&nbsp;May&nbsp;1945?{{refn|Karl Thieme's nomination from his unit was received by the ''[[Heerespersonalamt]]'' (HPA\u2014Army Personnel Office) on 10 April 1945 via [[teleprinter]]. ''Major'' [[Joachim Domaschk]] noted \"By no means sufficient! Requesting statement from [[OB West]]\", which was requested on 13 April. OB West responded on 24 April (entry date at the ''Heerespersonalamt'' on 28 April): \"Statement from OB West not possible, since nomination was not made via OB West\". ''Major'' Domaschk then decided on 28 April: \"[[Army Group B|''Heeresgruppe B'']], postpone!\" In this instance the nomination was not processed due to ''AHA 44 Ziff. 572'' but also because statements from his commanding officers could not be obtained anymore due to the capitulation. The nomination list for the higher grades of the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross also contains a note from 10 April 1945: postponed. A bestowal thus did not occur. The [[Association of Knight's Cross Recipients]] (AKCR) claims that the award was presented in accordance with the [[D\u00f6nitz-decree]]. This is illegal according to the [[Deutsche Dienststelle (WASt)]] and lacks legal justification. The sequential number \"156\" was assigned by the AKCR. Fellgiebel assigned the presentation date.<ref name=\"Scherzer p179\"/>|group=\"Note\"}}}} || {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Heinz|Thieme}}\n| [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] || <span style=\"display:none\">04-H</span>''[[Obergefreiter]]''<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || ''Richtsch\u00fctze'' (gunner) in the 14.(Panzerj\u00e4ger)/Grenadier-Regiment 446<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p421\"/>{{refn|According to Scherzer as ''Richtsch\u00fctze'' (gunner) in the 14./Grenadier-Regiment 446.<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/>|group=\"Note\"}} || style=\"background:#e3d9ff;\" align=\"left\" | {{dts|format=dmy|1944|January|20}}*<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || Died of wounds 17&nbsp;December&nbsp;1943<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p421\"/> || {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Helmut|Thierfelder}}\n| [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] || <span style=\"display:none\">10-H</span>''[[Oberfeldwebel]]''<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || ''[[Zugf\u00fchrer (military)|Zugf\u00fchrer]]'' (platoon leader) in the 6./Panzergrenadier-Regiment 33<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p421\"/><ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || {{dts|format=dmy|1944|September|2}}<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || {{center|\u2014}} || {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Werner|Thierfelder}}\n| [[Luftwaffe]] || <span style=\"display:none\">13-L</span>''[[Oberleutnant]]''{{refn|According to Scherzer as ''[[Oberleutnant]]'' of the [[Military reserve force|Reserves]] and pilot in the I./[[Zerst\u00f6rergeschwader 26]] \"Horst Wessel\".<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/>|group=\"Note\"|name=\"Thierfelder\"}} || ''[[Staffelkapit\u00e4n]]'' in the II./[[Zerst\u00f6rergeschwader 26]] \"Horst Wessel\"<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p421\"/><ref group=\"Note\" name=\"Thierfelder\"/> || {{dts|format=dmy|1941|December|10}}<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || {{center|\u2014}} || {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background:#ffdead;\" | {{sortname|Hans|Thiessen}}?{{refn|[[Hans Thiessen]]{{'}}s nomination by the troop was received by the ''[[Heerespersonalamt]]'' (HPA\u2014Army Staff Office) on 19 April 1945 and listed in the book \"''Verliehene Ritterkreuze''\" (Awarded Knight Crosses) under the sequential number 5147. ''[[Major (Germany)|Major]]'' [[Joachim Domaschk]] approved the nomination on 21 April 1945, noting \"Knight's Cross posthumously, yes\". A file card can be found in the record for rejected or unfinished nominations. The file card indicates no further information about further processing or whether the Knight's Cross was awarded. According to the [[Association of Knight's Cross Recipients]] (AKCR) the award was present in accordance with the [[D\u00f6nitz-decree]]. This is illegal according to the [[Deutsche Dienststelle (WASt)]] and lacks legal justification. The presentation date was assigned by [[Walther-Peer Fellgiebel]].<ref name=\"Scherzer p179\"/>|group=\"Note\"}}\n| [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] || <span style=\"display:none\">12-H</span>''[[Leutnant]]'' || Leader of the 2./Heeres-Flak-Abteilung \"Gro\u00dfdeutschland\"<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p421\"/> || style=\"background:#e3d9ff;\" align=\"left\" | {{dts|format=dmy|1945|May|9}}* || [[Killed in action]] 18&nbsp;February&nbsp;1945<ref name=\"Scherzer p179\"/> ||\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Johannes|Th\u00f6rner||Thoerner, Johannes}}\n| [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] || <span style=\"display:none\">14-H</span>''[[Hauptmann]]''<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || Deputy leader of the III./J\u00e4ger-Regiment 738<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p421\"/>{{refn|According to Scherzer as leader of the III./J\u00e4ger-Regiment 738.<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/>|group=\"Note\"}} || {{dts|format=dmy|1944|July|11}}<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || {{center|\u2014}} || {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Werner|Thofern}}\n| [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] || <span style=\"display:none\">12-H</span>''[[Leutnant]]''<ref name=\"Scherzer p742\"/> || ''[[Zugf\u00fchrer (military)|Zugf\u00fchrer]]'' (platoon leader) in the 1./Infanterie-Regiment 5 (motorized)<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p421\"/>{{refn|According to Scherzer as ''[[Zugf\u00fchrer (military)|Zugf\u00fchrer]]'' (platoon leader) in the 1./Sch\u00fctzen-Regiment 5.<ref