z und Ausbildungs Bataillon 49)<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p423\"/> || {{dts|format=dmy|1945|April|9}}<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/> || {{center|\u2014}} || {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Johannes|Tillmann}}\n| [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] || <span style=\"display:none\">12-H</span>''[[Leutnant]]'' of the [[Military reserve force|Reserves]]<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/> || Leader of the 10./Grenadier-Regiment 183<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/> || {{dts|format=dmy|1943|January|2}}<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/> || {{center|\u2014}} || {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|[Dr.] Wido|Tilmann|Wido Tilmann}}<ref name=\"[Dr.]\" group=\"Note\"/>\n| [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] || <span style=\"display:none\">12-H</span>''[[Leutnant]]''{{refn|According to Scherzer as ''[[Leutnant]]'' of the [[Military reserve force|Reserves]].<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/>|group=\"Note\"}} || ''[[Zugf\u00fchrer (military)|Zugf\u00fchrer]]'' (platoon leader) in the 2./Pionier-Bataillon 297<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p423\"/><ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/> || {{dts|format=dmy|1941|December|22}}<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/> || {{center|\u2014}} || {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Erich|Timm}}\n| [[Luftwaffe]] || <span style=\"display:none\">15-L</span>''[[Major (Germany)|Major]]''<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/> || Commander of Fallschirmj\u00e4ger-Regiment 12<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p423\"/>{{refn|According to Scherzer as commander of Fallschirmj\u00e4ger-Sturm-Regiment (12).<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/>|group=\"Note\"}} || {{dts|format=dmy|1944|October|3}}<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/> || {{center|\u2014}} || {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Heinrich|Timm}}\n| [[Kriegsmarine]] || <span style=\"display:none\">15-M</span>''[[Korvettenkapit\u00e4n]]''<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/> || Commander of {{GS|U-862||2}}<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/><ref name=\"Fellgiebel p424\">Fellgiebel 2000, p. 424.</ref> || {{dts|format=dmy|1944|September|17}}<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/> || {{center|\u2014}} || {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"background:#ffdead;\" | {{sortname|Heinz|Timpe}}?{{refn|No evidence of the award can be found in the [[German Federal Archives]]. The presentation, according to [[Walther-Peer Fellgiebel]], was made by ''[[Feldmarschall]]'' [[Ferdinand Sch\u00f6rner]] based on the empowerment of 3 May 1945. According to Franz Thomas and G\u00fcnter Wegmann, authors of the book series \"''Die Ritterkreuztr\u00e4ger der Deutschen Wehrmacht 1939\u20131945\u2014The Knight's Cross Bearers of the German Wehrmacht 1939\u20131945''\", the presentation was authorized via radio message from the [[Army Group Centre|Heeresgruppe Mitte]] via the combat commander of the [[20th Panzer Division|20. Panzer-Division]], and communicated by the chief of the Stabsbatterie, Leutnant Cornehl, near the [[Tepl\u00e1 Abbey]] near [[Mari\u00e1nsk\u00e9 L\u00e1zn\u011b]]. The presentation was noted in [[Heinz Timpe]]'s paybook. Presumably Timpe had been nominated three times for Knight\u2019s Cross, first time in September 1944, in January 1945 and April 1945. The Federal Archive holds neither record of nomination, rejection nor a file card of any proceedings. The order commission of the [[Association of Knight's Cross Recipients]] (AKCR) never processed his case either.<ref name=\"Scherzer p180\">Scherzer 2007, p. 180.</ref>|group=\"Note\"}}\n| [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] || <span style=\"display:none\">12-H</span>''[[Leutnant]]'' || Chief of the 1./Sturmgesch\u00fctz-Brigade 300 (F)<ref name=\"Fellgiebel p424\"/> || {{dts|format=dmy|1945|May|7}} || {{center|\u2014}} || {{center|\u2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{sortname|Adolf-Hilmar von|Tippelskirch}}\n| [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] || <span style=\"display:none\">13-H</span>''[[Oberleutnant]]''<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/> || Chief of the 1./Artillerie-Regiment 3 (motorized)<ref name=\"Scherzer p746\"/><ref name=\"Fellgiebel p424\"/> || {{dts|format=